Bah! Perl is 5.8.8. That was released back in 2006. Still, it works. I got a chance to see the code that others were running:<p><pre><code>    #!/usr/bin/perl

    use File::Find;
    my @found;
    find(
        sub {push @found => $File::Find::name if -f $_},
        '.'
    );
    for my $file (@found) {
        if ( open my $fh, '<', $file ) {
            my $contents = do { local $/; <$fh> };
            print <<"END";
    File: $file

    $contents
    ------------------------
    END
        }
        else {
        	print "Could not open $file ($!)
";
        }
    }
</code></pre>
<i>Update</i>: all things considered, seeing people trying to run the following code doesn't increase my faith in humanity:<p><pre><code>    #!/bin/bash
    mv $0 "8======D~~~~"</code></pre>
